    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2152859957" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2152859957" />
    <a title="Paul LaFontaine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/63035896-paul-lafontaine"><img alt="Paul LaFontaine" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1482781238p2/63035896.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2152859957?book_show_action=true">Oct 14, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paul LaFontaine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paul LaFontaine" href="/user/show/63035896-paul-lafontaine">Paul LaFontaine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2152859957" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13999146064857101011">A disfigured English man from the late 1800&apos;s is sheltered by a doctor who discovers him trying to make money as a freak show attraction. Society embraces him and he becomes a chance for people to reflect on their own lives. <br/><br/>A short play on a fairly well-known topic, I liked the insights that people derived from the interaction with the protagonist. The issue of how and who &quot;views&quot; the oddity runs throughout and makes for a thoughtful experience. <br/><br/>Recommend</span>
  <span id="freeText13999146064857101011" style="display:none">A disfigured English man from the late 1800's is sheltered by a doctor who discovers him trying to make money as a freak show attraction. Society embraces him and he becomes a chance for people to reflect on their own lives. <br /><br />A short play on a fairly well-known topic, I liked the insights that people derived from the interaction with the protagonist. The issue of how and who "views" the oddity runs throughout and makes for a thoughtful experience. <br /><br />Recommend</span>
