<span id="freeTextContainer5738254104911751307">&quot;The Elephant Man&quot; by Bernard Pomerance is a tragic story of John Merrick, man who was very sick. He had a mutated skin and (because of genetic mutations) extremely large head.<br/>Action begins at 1884 in London, times when illness like this was taken as a curse or punishment from evil for sins. He was struggling to find his place in a world when he&apos;s a show for people. He&apos;s being betrayed by everyone until a famous doctor, royal surgeon, Trevers decides to take care of him. <br/>Then his life begins to </span>
  <span id="freeText5738254104911751307" style="display:none">"The Elephant Man" by Bernard Pomerance is a tragic story of John Merrick, man who was very sick. He had a mutated skin and (because of genetic mutations) extremely large head.<br />Action begins at 1884 in London, times when illness like this was taken as a curse or punishment from evil for sins. He was struggling to find his place in a world when he's a show for people. He's being betrayed by everyone until a famous doctor, royal surgeon, Trevers decides to take care of him. <br />Then his life begins to look at least a little more normal. <br />He have to learn how normal, ordinary human beings act, because he never even had a chance to know how worlds work. <br />He make friends with Bishop How, actress Mrs. Kendal and many other people. <br />I liked this book very much and I think that it's worth reading, because it covers many interesting psychological subjects.<br />Also I recommend to watch a film as well, because it really is great.</span>
