        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer93324355" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5786528921443446758"><u>The Elephant Man</u> by Bernard Pomerance (Grove Press 1979) (612.0). This is a play based upon the life of John Merrick, the original “Elephant Man” who was so named for a repulsive skin condition from which he suffered. Horribly deformed, Merrick lived in Victorian London, England and was exhibited at a young age in circus sideshows. He was rescued by a physician who took over his care. Merrick, who was a kind and gentle soul, eventually found a home inside a hospital. He came to meet many members</span>
  <span id="freeText5786528921443446758" style="display:none"><u>The Elephant Man</u> by Bernard Pomerance (Grove Press 1979) (612.0). This is a play based upon the life of John Merrick, the original “Elephant Man” who was so named for a repulsive skin condition from which he suffered. Horribly deformed, Merrick lived in Victorian London, England and was exhibited at a young age in circus sideshows. He was rescued by a physician who took over his care. Merrick, who was a kind and gentle soul, eventually found a home inside a hospital. He came to meet many members of royalty and society before an early death. This is a very moving play and a heart-rending story. My rating: 7/10, finished 1982. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5786528921443446758" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
