<span id="freeTextContainer12234574306825508258">An enjoyable read with some scorching lines. The pacing was awkward and a bit unclear with Merrick&apos;s life in the hospital. The idea that the hospital&apos;s sanitizing of Merrick didn&apos;t allow him the authentic human experience was saddening. Merrick was so hopeful at the beginning of his stay too, with his ideas about Romeo and Juliet and his naïvete. It&apos;s a quick read.</span>
